description: Returns the OpenSearch Serverless-managed interface VPC endpoints associated with the current account. For more information, see Access Amazon OpenSearch Serverless using an interface endpoint.

parameters.name: vpcEndpointFilters
parameters.description: Filter the results according to the current status of the VPC endpoint. Possible statuses are CREATING, DELETING, UPDATING, ACTIVE, and FAILED. status (string) --- The current status of the endpoint.

nested_params.name: status
nested_params.description: The current status of the endpoint.

nested_items.name: vpcEndpointSummaries
nested_items.description: Details about each VPC endpoint, including the name and current status.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the endpoint.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The current status of the endpoint.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: When nextToken is returned, there are more results available. The value of nextToken is a unique pagination token for each page. Make the call again using the returned token to retrieve the next page.
